# File Structure

**Objective**: Standardize file structure by following the principle "1 component = 1 complete file" inspired by Shadcn UI.

**Context**: To apply for unifying code style and conventions.

## Explanation

Each component, hook, or service must live in its own file with everything it needs: types, helpers, styles (via Tailwind). This approach improves readability and facilitates reuse.

**Key principles:**

- **1 component = 1 file**: a file contains a single main component.
- **Everything in the file**: types, variants, internal helpers are in the same file.
- **Named export**: always use named exports.
- **No artificial separation**: don't separate types in a separate file unless shared.

## Practical Implementation Example

**Structure of a complete component (Shadcn UI style):**

```tsx
// src/components/ui/button.tsx
import * as React from "react";
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

// Component variants (in the same file)
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary-500 text-white hover:bg-primary-600",
        destructive: "bg-red-500 text-white hover:bg-red-600",
        outline: "border border-gray-300 bg-transparent hover:bg-gray-100",
        ghost: "hover:bg-gray-100",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",
        sm: "h-9 px-3",
        lg: "h-11 px-8",
        icon: "h-10 w-10",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);

// Component types (in the same file)
export interface ButtonProps
  extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
  asChild?: boolean;
}

// Main component
export const Button = React.forwardRef<HTMLButtonElement, ButtonProps>(
  ({ className, variant, size, ...props }, ref) => {
    return (
      <button
        className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}
        ref={ref}
        {...props}
      />
    );
  }
);

Button.displayName = "Button";
```

